00021 #include <stdio.h>
00022 #include <stdlib.h>
00023 #include <time.h>
00024 
00025 #include "test-harness.h"
00026 
00027 #include "dbprim.h"
00028 #include "dbprim_int.h"
00029 
00030 RCSTAG("@(#)$Id$");
00031 
00032 TEST_PROG(t_smat, "Test sparse matrix functionality")
00033 
00034 #define SMAT_HEAD_CNT   32
00035 
00036 /* this is so complicated because SMAT_HEAD_CNT is likely the maximum number
00037  * of bits representable in an unsigned long, so we have to look out for
00038  * overflows.
00039  */
00040 #define SMAT_HEAD_MASK  ((((0x01lu << (SMAT_HEAD_CNT - 1)) - 1) << 1) | 0x01lu)
00041 
00042 static smat_head_t rows[SMAT_HEAD_CNT];
00043 static smat_head_t columns[SMAT_HEAD_CNT];
00044 static struct assoc_s {
00045   unsigned long assoc[SMAT_HEAD_CNT];
00046 } associations;
00047 
00048 #define SMAT_ASSOC_CNT  (32 * 4)
00049 
00050 /* Set all bits in the struct assoc_s to one... */
00051 static void
00052 set_ones(struct assoc_s *assoc)
00053 {
00054   int i;
00055 
00056   for (i = 0; i < SMAT_HEAD_CNT; i++) /* walk through them all... */
00057     assoc->assoc[i] = SMAT_HEAD_MASK; /* set the bits */
00058 }
00059 
00060 /* Clear all bits in the struct assoc_s... */
00061 static void
00062 set_zeros(struct assoc_s *assoc)
00063 {
00064   int i;
00065 
00066   for (i = 0; i < SMAT_HEAD_CNT; i++) /* walk through them all... */
00067     assoc->assoc[i] = 0; /* set the bits */
00068 }
00069 
00070 /* is everything zeroed? */
00071 static int
00072 check_zeros(struct assoc_s *assoc)
00073 {
00074   int i;
00075 
00076   for (i = 0; i < SMAT_HEAD_CNT; i++) /* walk through them all... */
00077     if (assoc->assoc[i]) /* if an element's not zero... */
00078       return 0;
00079 
00080   return 1; /* everything is zeroed. */
00081 }
00082 
00083 /* macros to diddle individual bits in the association tracker */
00084 #define set_assoc(ass, row, column) \
00085                         ((ass)->assoc[(row)] |=  (0x01lu << (column)))
00086 #define clr_assoc(ass, row, column) \
00087                         ((ass)->assoc[(row)] &= ~(0x01lu << (column)))
00088 #define chk_assoc(ass, row, column) \
00089                         ((ass)->assoc[(row)] &   (0x01lu << (column)))
00090 
00091 int
00092 main(int argc, char **argv)
00093 {
00094   unsigned long err;
00095   smat_table_t tab; /* a sparse matrix table to play with... */
00096   smat_entry_t *se = 0;
00097   int i, rt, ct;
00098   struct assoc_s visited;
00099 
00100   srand(time(0)); /* seed random number generator */
00101 
00102   /* Let's test st_init first... */
00103   TEST(t_smat, st_init, "Test that st_init() may be called",
00104        (!(err = st_init(&tab, 0, 0, 0, 6)) &&
00105         st_modulus(&tab) == 7), FATAL(0),
00106        ("st_init() call successful"),
00107        ("st_init() call failed with error %lu modulus %lu", err,
00108         st_modulus(&tab)));
00109 
00110   /* Now try some sh_inits... */
00111   TEST_DECL(t_smat, sh_init, "Test that sh_init() may be called")
00112   for (i = 0; i < SMAT_HEAD_CNT; i++)
00113     if ((err = sh_init(&rows[i], SMAT_LOC_FIRST, (void *)i)) ||
00114         (err = sh_init(&columns[i], SMAT_LOC_SECOND, (void *)i)))
00115       FAIL(TEST_NAME(sh_init), FATAL(0), "sh_init() failed with error %lu",
00116            err);
00117   PASS(TEST_NAME(sh_init), "sh_init() calls successful");
00118 
00119   /* OK, create some associations... */
00120   TEST_DECL(t_smat, st_add, "Test that st_add() adds elements to a sparse "
00121             "matrix")
00122   set_zeros(&associations); /* clear the associations */
00123   for (i = 0; i < SMAT_ASSOC_CNT; i++) {
00124     rt = rand() % SMAT_HEAD_CNT; /* select row and column elements... */
00125     ct = rand() % SMAT_HEAD_CNT;
00126 
00127     if (chk_assoc(&associations, rt, ct))
00128       continue; /* only create unique associations */
00129 
00130     fprintf(stderr, "Creating association %d<->%d\n", rt, ct);
00131 
00132     /* add the association; note that ll_add()'s been tested, so
00133      * we don't have to test with other LINK_LOC_* values.  (Well,
00134      * perhaps we should, but it's tough to do it here...)
00135      */
00136     if ((err = st_add(&tab, 0, &rows[rt], LINK_LOC_HEAD, 0, &columns[ct],
00137                       LINK_LOC_HEAD, 0)))
00138       FAIL(TEST_NAME(st_add), FATAL(0), "st_add() failed with error %lu", err);
00139 
00140     set_assoc(&associations, rt, ct); /* remember the association */
00141   }
00142   PASS(TEST_NAME(st_add), "st_add() added associations properly");
00143 
00144   /* Can we look them up? */
00145   TEST_DECL(t_smat, st_find, "Test that st_find() can locate elements in a "
00146             "sparse matrix")
00147   for (set_ones(&visited); !check_zeros(&visited);
00148        clr_assoc(&visited, rt, ct)) {
00149     rt = rand() % SMAT_HEAD_CNT; /* select row and column elements... */
00150     ct = rand() % SMAT_HEAD_CNT;
00151 
00152     fprintf(stderr, "Looking up association %d<->%d\n", rt, ct);
00153 
00154     /* look up the association */
00155     err = st_find(&tab, &se, &rows[rt], &columns[ct]);
00156 
00157     /* check the error value... */
00158     if (err != (chk_assoc(&associations, rt, ct) ? 0 : DB_ERR_NOENTRY))
00159       FAIL(TEST_NAME(st_find), FATAL(0), "st_find() failed with error %lu",
00160            err);
00161     if (!err && ((int)se_object(se, SMAT_LOC_FIRST) != rt ||
00162                  (int)se_object(se, SMAT_LOC_SECOND) != ct))
00163       FAIL(TEST_NAME(st_find), FATAL(0), "st_find() found wrong entry; "
00164            "expected %d/%d, found %d/%d", rt, ct,
00165            (int)se_object(se, SMAT_LOC_FIRST),
00166            (int)se_object(se, SMAT_LOC_SECOND));
00167 
00168     fprintf(stderr, err ? "No such association\n" : "Found association\n");
00169   }
00170   PASS(TEST_NAME(st_find), "st_find() calls successful");
00171 
00172   /* Now try to remove some entries... */
00173   TEST_DECL(t_smat, st_remove, "Test that st_remove() can remove elements in "
00174             "a sparse matrix")
00175   while (st_count(&tab) > SMAT_ASSOC_CNT / 2) {
00176     rt = rand() % SMAT_HEAD_CNT; /* select row and column elements... */
00177     ct = rand() % SMAT_HEAD_CNT;
00178 
00179     if (!chk_assoc(&associations, rt, ct))
00180       continue; /* only try to remove associations that exist */
00181 
00182     fprintf(stderr, "Looking up association %d<->%d for removal\n", rt, ct);
00183 
00184     if ((err = st_find(&tab, &se, &rows[rt], &columns[ct])) ||
00185         (err = st_remove(&tab, se)))
00186       FAIL(TEST_NAME(st_remove), FATAL(0), "st_find() failed to find "
00187            "association %d/%d or st_remove() failed to remove it", rt, ct);
00188 
00189     fprintf(stderr, "Association removed\n");
00190 
00191     clr_assoc(&associations, rt, ct);
00192   }
00193   PASS(TEST_NAME(st_remove), "st_remove() calls successful");
00194 
00195   return 0;
00196 }
